					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">I don't think I'd bother trying to make the linker sort out unions on such a small scale. You can always just create alias labels. Maybe it's not as convenient as .res but for individual functions you probably don't have a lot of allocations to make. Doing it manually shouldn't be too onerous:<br /><div class="codetitle"><b>Code:</b></div><div class="codecontent">; alllocate scratchpad<br />.segment &quot;ZP&quot;: zeropage<br />scratchpad: .res 32<br /><br />...<br /><br />; alias new allocations from scratchpad for each function as needed<br /><br />.proc myfunc<br />param_a = scratchpad + 0<br />param_b = scratchpad + 1<br />temp_c&nbsp; = scartchpad + 2<br />&nbsp; &nbsp; ; code goes here<br />&nbsp; &nbsp; rts<br />.endproc<br /><br />; bonus: using .proc puts these aliases in their own scope, so they don't pollute the global space, and you can also access them from outside the function:<br /><br />&nbsp; &nbsp; stx myfunc::param_a<br />&nbsp; &nbsp; sty myfunc::param_b<br />&nbsp; &nbsp; jsr myfunc</div><br /><br /><em>Edit: ZP segment must be identified as zeropage.</em></div>

					
							<br /><br />
							<span class="gensmall">Last edited by <a href="./memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=5165">rainwarrior</a> on Tue Nov 03, 2015 11:18 am, edited 1 time in total.</span>
