						<div class="postbody">Ah, I didn't realize subsequent uses of .segment with no qualifier will assume the previous state. I was just going by some quick tests I threw together, i.e.<br /><div class="codetitle"><b>Code:</b></div><div class="codecontent">; this creates an error:<br /><br />.segment &quot;ZP&quot; ; no specification: assumes absolute<br />.segment &quot;ZP&quot;: zeropage ; error<br /><br />; VS this apparently does not:<br /><br />.segment &quot;ZP&quot;: zeropage<br />.segment &quot;ZP&quot; ; OK: assumes previous usage</div></div>

